Title: Senior Software Engineer
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

The Senior Software Engineer will be a part of the Group Billing Team and help modernize our Online Billing Application and Group Management Experience. Along with writing effective code, the position will be responsible for designing, building, delivering and maintaining a highly scalable set of products and applications. The incumbent will use industry best practices and work collaboratively with cross-functional team of product managers, UX designers, architects, principal engineers, software engineers, test automation team and DevOps engineers.

The Senior Software Engineer will be part of an engineering team that builds and supports amazing customer-facing products that will drive the next generation of Delta Dental Digital Experience.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Performs as a key contributor to an engineering team that builds and supports exceptional products that provide innovative solutions to challenging business use cases, existing system and operational problems.
Participates in architectural design, system analysis, and programming activities on application software; this may often require independent research and study.
Develops high-quality and production-ready software by using best-practice data structures, algorithms, design patterns, and frameworks that are maintainable, scalable, responsive, and secure.
Writes highest quality code with utmost attention to scalability, security and performance and with an end-to-end mindset from conception to delivery and production support, owning specifications, quality, release deployments and monitoring of production health.
Produces complete, simple, and readable technical documentation for everything developed and maintains a team culture of documenting everything.
Tests and ensures quality of all code that developed in line with principles of test-driven development and continuous delivery, utilizing test automation frameworks wherever possible.
Participates in code-reviews, provides technical guidance and mentors software engineers.
Collaborates closely with Engineering leadership, Product Managers, Designers, Test Automation and other teams and business units to define, prioritize, sequence and scope business and functional requirements and drive results.
Instruments infrastructure and application performance monitoring, capacity management, alerting, tools instrumentation and metrics (KPI) management.
Performs impact assessment of product (hardware, software) upgrades.
Assists in planning, coordinating, and executing engineering projects.
Supports and collaborates with other Engineers through evaluation, design analysis, and development phases.
Maintains knowledge, ensures competency and compliance with policies and procedures, in order to be the technical expert while collaborating with cross-functional teams.
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

4+ years experience with a Degree in Computer Science and/or equivalent technical education and experience.
Expertise with Java/J2EE experience including frameworks such as Spring MVC and Hibernate.
Experience with Spring Boot, microservices, NoSQL, caching and message queue technologies
Integration experience consuming REST Services.
Cloud experience with AWS or Azure or Google or PCF.
Ability to understand business plans and apply that information into the development of an IT business case.
Anticipates problems, resistance or likely objections and takes action to resolve them.
Ability to lead and manage small to large enterprise network implementations or changes.
Ability to guide, train and mentor associate engineers.
Highly skilled in developing quantitative cost/benefit analysis to measure improvements.
Proficient in organizational processes as well as capable of assessing and initiating change of such processes.
Demonstrates an in-depth knowledge and application of competency and can consult as well as lead others in its application.
Strong communication (written and verbal) and presentation skills.
Knowledge of agile development methodologies.
Ability to develop and maintain key vendor relationships with a focus on technology currency and best practices.
Life-long learner, process improver.

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

Rewards to make you smile! We don't just want to make our customers happy - we want to give our employees a reason to smile, too. Delta Dental's comprehensive benefits package includes:

Generous paid time off plus 12 holidays and your birthday off!
Low-cost premium medical insurance options
100% paid dental and vision insurance
Generous 401(k) matching and flat contribution
Social responsibility and volunteer opportunities, including 16 paid volunteer hours annually
Employee LiveWell program, focusing on overall employee well-being

ABOUT THE TEAM

At Delta Dental, our success is only as strong as the people who execute it! We take enormous pride in being the nation's most recognized and widely-used provider of dental insurance - and we've come this far by living our core values of innovation, excellence, service and trust. Our vision is to motivate and empower every employee so that we're all inspired to take exceptional care of our customers, providers and ourselves. We believe in integrity, accountability, collaboration, and giving every employee equitable opportunity for their voice to be heard and development to be fostered.

If you're excited about the prospect of transforming the future of health care and growing in your career, join our smile revolution!

To see some of the smiling faces behind Delta Dental and to learn more about what our values and culture look like in action, connect with us on social media: Delta Dental Ins. on Facebook and Instagram, #LifeatDDins on Facebook and Instagram , Delta Dental Ins. on Twitter and Delta Dental Ins. on LinkedIn .

We are part of the Delta Dental Plans Association, a network of companies that provides dental coverage to 74 million people in the U.S. Delta Dental of California, Delta Dental of New York, Inc., Delta Dental of Pennsylvania and Delta Dental Insurance Company, together with our affiliate companies, form one of the nation's largest dental benefits delivery systems, covering 33 million enrollees. All of our companies are members, or affiliates of members, of the Delta Dental Plans Association, a network of 39 Delta Dental companies throughout the country.

Delta Dental is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to building and maintaining a diverse and inclusive workplace for all employees. Applicants will not be discriminated against because of race, color, religion, creed, national origin, ancestry, citizenship status, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, gender or identity expression, age, disability, marital status, medical status, veteran status or any other status protected under federal, state, or local law. In addition to federal law requirements, Delta Dental complies with applicable state and local laws governing nondiscrimination in employment in every location in which the company has facilities. This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training.

Unfortunately, our Delta Dental Enterprise is unable to hire individuals residing in Alaska, North Dakota, Nebraska, Hawaii, Oklahoma, Vermont, Maine, West Virginia, New Hampshire, Wyoming, Puerto Rico or other US Territories at this time.

Proof of eligibility to work in the United States must be provided if selected for hire.

Delta Dental* has enacted a COVID-19 vaccination policy to protect all employees and the communities we serve due to the ongoing impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic. Accordingly, we require all employees to be fully vaccinated for COVID-19. Title: Senior Software Development Engineer, Adobe CQ5
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

The Senior Software Engineer will help build the Next Gen Applications Suite. Along with writing effective code, the position will be responsible for designing, building, delivering and maintaining a highly scalable set of products and applications. The incumbent will use industry best practices and work collaboratively with cross-functional team of product managers, UX designers, architects, principal engineers, software engineers, test automation team and DevOps engineers.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Performs as a key contributor to an engineering team that builds and supports exceptional products that provide innovative solutions to challenging business use cases, existing system and operational problems.
Participates in architectural design, system analysis, and programming activities on application software; this may often require independent research and study.
Develops high-quality and production-ready software by using best-practice data structures, algorithms, design patterns, and frameworks that are maintainable, scalable, responsive, and secure.
Writes highest quality code with utmost attention to scalability, security and performance and with an end-to-end mindset from conception to delivery and production support, owning specifications, quality, release deployments and monitoring of production health.
Produces complete, simple, and readable technical documentation for everything developed and maintains a team culture of documenting everything.
Tests and ensures quality of all code that developed in line with principles of test-driven development and continuous delivery, utilizing test automation frameworks wherever possible.
Participates in code-reviews, provides technical guidance and mentors software engineers.
Collaborates closely with Engineering leadership, Product Managers, Designers, Test Automation and other teams and business units to define, prioritize, sequence and scope business and functional requirements and drive results.
Instruments infrastructure and application performance monitoring, capacity management, alerting, tools instrumentation and metrics (KPI) management.
Performs impact assessment of product (hardware, software) upgrades.
Assists in planning, coordinating, and executing engineering projects.
Supports and collaborates with other Engineers through evaluation, design analysis, and development phases.
Maintains knowledge, ensures competency and compliance with policies and procedures, in order to be the technical expert while collaborating with cross-functional teams.
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

Minimum of 4+ years of experience alongside a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or equivalent technical field.
2+ years of experience with developing and deploying applications on Azure or similar cloud platform.
10 + years of experience designing and developing highly scalable and secure Applications and Products.
Experience building web applications with Oracle ADF.
4+ years of experience building production application with Spring framework.
Experience in Full Stack Front-End development. Solid understanding of HTML5 and CSS3.
5-7 years of strong experience in building and consuming of Restful Web service, JSON based request response.
Experience working with popular JavaScript tools and Frameworks.
2+ years of experience writing & debugging SQL development.
4+ years of experience with the design and implementation of low-latency, high-availability and performant applications.
Proficiency with Chrome and/or other browser Developer Tools.
Proficiency with Git/GitHub, SVN or other distributed version control systems.
Knowledge on user-centered design, progressive enhancement and graceful degradation, accessibility, SEO, responsive design, and website performance.
Experience with Scrum, Agile Process.
Continuous learning to stay current with the changing technology landscape.
Nice to have - experience with Azure; experience with Test Driven Development, Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery; experience with logging tools like Splunk or ELK; understanding of Relational, No SQL databases.
Ability to understand business plans and apply that information into the development of an IT business case.
Anticipates problems, resistance or likely objections and takes action to resolve them.
Ability to lead and manage small to large enterprise network implementations or changes.
Ability to guide, train and mentor associate engineers.
Highly skilled in developing quantitative cost/benefit analysis to measure improvements.
Proficient in organizational processes as well as capable of assessing and initiating change of such processes.
Demonstrates an in-depth knowledge and application of competency and can consult as well as lead others in its application.
Strong communication (written and verbal) and presentation skills.
Knowledge of agile development methodologies.
Ability to develop and maintain key vendor relationships with a focus on technology currency and best practices.
Life-long learner, process improver.

Title: Senior Software Development Engineer, Adobe CQ5
Job_Description:
ABOUT US
We are a well-funded Series B ($81MM) high growth startup headquartered in Seattle, with employees throughout the United States and EMEA. Most of our roles are remote-first and we offer a diverse, respectful, fun, and collaborative environment to work in. We're currently in the start-up sweet spot with sufficiently low risk and yet still the potential of massive upside.
At Edge Delta, we are building the world's first edge observability platform allowing our customers to analyze their data as it's created, where it's created. Embracing the freedom to decouple where you analyze your data from where it's stored, this unique take on DevOps, Security, and SRE lets you consume and analyze outputs (logs, metrics, events, traces, telemetry) at the source  how we've defined the edge.
Our customers escape the constraints and architectural limitations of traditional centralized systems by utilizing our lightweight and ultra-fast agent, distributed architecture, and stream processing capabilities. Ultimately, Edge Delta provides the scalability the market needs without previous technical or financial limitations, unlocking limitless data analysis, faster intelligence, and automated anomaly detection.

Title: Program Manager Information Technology, Onboard Services
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

This job is responsible for helping the organization reach its development roadmap goals as well as providing support for strategic Agile initiatives. Makes connections across teams and work streams to drive identification and facilitation of interdependencies. Partners with Business, Technology, and Product Management organizations to drive for clarity on objectives, priorities, and measures. Influences change and drives continuous improvement through feedback and measurement to identify and act on areas of opportunity. Advances overall delivery effectiveness through coaching, mentoring, and training.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Manages Scrum Masters and with interaction accountability for the wider product and technology teams.
Develops and implements strategic, large and/or multi-phased initiatives from original concept through final implementation, creating plans, schedules, estimates, allocation of people, and status sharing in an Agile environment.
Supports teams to consider shared services and cross-team alignment at all levels of planning
Evolves quantitative and qualitative measures of value, outcome, velocity, morale, and satisfaction to ensure the use of effective KPIs are integrated into delivery and beyond.
Enables productivity by fostering cross-team communication, empowerment, and accountability. Help teams manage and resolve interdependencies, risks, conflicts, and impediments.
Works with product management, technical leadership, subject matter experts, and other stakeholders as appropriate to ensure all perspectives are being considered throughout planning and delivery.
Applies teamwork, risk management, and communication to lead key initiatives/teams that may not fall under traditional Agile management; enables team communication and effective engagement with product management and other key stakeholders.
Integrates the development of best practices, standards, procedures, and quality objectives.
Focuses on improving execution, effectiveness, and quality of service in all software delivery teams; executes the scaling of processes to support product portfolios, major initiatives, and alignment of cross-team dependencies for delivery.
Demonstrates leadership and be a role model for creating a collaborative and Agile culture; brings new ideas, continually challenges the status quo, and promotes a continuous improvement mindset throughout the organization.
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

8+ years of overall experience along with a Bachelor's degree.
1+ years of supervisory/management experience; 3+ years of management or supervisory experience preferred.
Demonstrated success driving agile maturity across a program or portfolio of teams.
Proven track record of motivating teams, instilling accountability for value delivery.
Solid understanding of software development life cycle models as well as expert knowledge of both Agile and traditional project management principles and practices and the ability to blend them together in the right proportions to fit a business environment.
Strong understanding of the end to end enterprise operating model.
Proven capability of managing multiple priorities effectively and performing under tight deadlines.
Demonstrate creative problem solving in situations with ambiguity in order to ensure forward delivery progress in a timely manner.
Expert knowledge of portfolio, program, change management and strategic capabilities.
Looked to as a trusted, capable leader able to drive a program independently, engaging senior leadership at the right level and right time.
Strong team player with proven ability to lead through influence.
Highly collaborative with a track record of effective cross-functional leadership and proven track record to influence at all levels.
Experience developing and deploying new processes for effective scaling.
Balanced business/technical background. Sufficient level of technical knowledge to provide highly credible leadership to technology teams. Ability to accurately and objectively evaluate complex project risks and issues, and communicate these effectively to business stakeholders.
Preferred certifications include SAFe Scrum Master / Certified Scrum Master.

Title: Program Manager Information Technology, Onboard Services
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

The Agile Coach will be a strong expert practitioner with skills to educate and help mature multiple scrum teams, with deep knowledge of the practicalities in the agile/lean space. The coach will have a range of skills in teaching, mentoring, facilitating and professional coaching, and their own delivery style which will be a blend of all these techniques. The coach will also work with senior leadership to increase team effectiveness and implement Agile principles.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Works with Scrum Teams, programs and leaders to adopt new ways of thinking, and adapt the way they work.
Guides and leads the team to follow agile principles and practices.
Facilitates agile discipline to cultivate effective team dynamics and nurture team to self-direct, embrace and exhibit the agile mindset.
Builds commitment from different org level leaders (Product, Technology and Business directors and VPs) to enhance organizational agility.
Designs and leads new team workshops in complex agile concepts in coordination with other Agile Coaches.
Guides teams through standard daily activities, with intention of upskilling the Scrum Master, Product Owner/team, and transferring accountability after initial sprints (model, coach, and empower).
Coaches to positively reinforce an Agile mindset, practices, and skills to teams, individuals and leaders
Mentors Scrum Masters, Product Owners, Product Managers and Technology Managers to enable innovative servant leadership and empowerment of teams.
Leads process improvement initiatives that have enterprise impact.
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

Minimum of 8 years experience in the Agile adoption space in addition to a Bachelor's degree.
Experience with Agile Coaching techniques through Agile Coaching Institute or CRR Global, or Co-Active coaching skills.
Skillful in Kanban and lean methods and scaling methods like LeSS or Scrum @ Scale.
Understanding of applying Agile assessment techniques to measure agile maturity.
Awareness and knowledge of CI-CD/DevOps and Cloud space to enable the organization navigate challenges in adopting Agile in those environments.
Knowledgeable about applying Capex/Opex financial accounting in the Agile space.
Expert in facilitation, situational awareness, conflict resolution.
Expert practitioner with skills to educate and help mature Scrum teams.
Expert in various agile methodologies, SAFe, Scrum, Kanban, XP.
Proven ability to train, onboard, coach and mentor others.
Ability to effectively communicate across multiple levels within Scrum Teams.
Demonstrated experience with Visioning, Road-mapping, Release Planning, Iterative Planning/Continuous Planning (Scrum/Kanban events).
Strategic perspective in enabling planning, continuous improvement, and thoughtful data driven decisions.
Ability to maintain an enterprise perspective and partner with Senior Leadership.
SAFE SPC Certification (recommended).
CSP, CEC or equivalent certification preferable not required.

Title: Senior Software Development Engineer, TechOps Technology Solutions
Job_Description:
Job Description

Requisition #32600-Sr. Test Engineer - Specialized
[Atlanta, 30377], Georgia - United States | Posted - 05/05/22

Overview
Qualifications:As a Software Development Engineer in Test (SDET) you will help deliver the quality and performance of large scale, big data, custom hardware multi-platform middleware that includes; Microservice and, API interfaces. Incumbents in this position are experienced, hands on, self-motivated and can work collaboratively in a continuous integration environment. This role involves working closely with Subject Matter Experts to understand a complex domain and product. The SDET focuses on contributing to the development of functional component tests, integration tests and end-to-end tests through open-source test frameworks for overall system testing within an Agile environment. You must be responsive, flexible, a critical thinker and able to succeed within an open collaborative peer environment. The SDET must have a strong understanding of user and process requirements and the ability to ensure those requirements are met through high-quality test plans, meticulous execution, and thorough documentation. Job Location:  Must be located in Atlanta or willing to relocate.  This is not a 100% remote position. Key responsibilities:  Test data eventing output from Flight Schedules, Flight Movement, Ship Operations, Gates, Task Tracking, Crew and Flight Planning.  Validate data aggregation in AWS DynamoDB.  Design tools for unit, functional, and performance.  Participate in code inspections.  Propose improvements to our existing processes and build automated tools, libraries, and utilities to improve the teams speed, quality and efficiency is a plus.  Own the design and implementation of tests that will insure end-to-end quality of major deliverables  Work closely with Subject Matter Experts, Product Owners, Test Engineers from other teams to execute a coordinated integration test plan.  Integrate tests and infrastructure automation into the CI/CD pipeline.  Contribute to agile development. What you need to succeed: Critical  2 to 5 years of experience in Information Technology with expertise in creating, executing and documenting test cases. Title: Field Applications Engineer
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

This position is responsible for implementing, deploying, and supporting Production and Development Windows systems applications that provide services to our business and technical staff. Responsibilities include identifying and correcting performance issues, providing support to applications developers, infrastructure teams, DevOps and end-users. You will have the ability/experience in designing automated solutions, process improvement, Capacity and Performance Management, performance monitoring, software installations/upgrades, technical assistance, server security management, hardware recommendations and procurement. In depth working knowledge of Windows Operating Systems, storage, network, databases, DevOps tools, PowerShell scripting and programming are required.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Manages systems and applications based on the Windows Server System platform.
Performs day-to-day Windows application administration, performance monitoring, backup and recovery, triage support, troubleshooting, root cause analysis, and problem resolution.
Performs/assists in periodic and emergency system and patch maintenance while minimizing client impact to the greatest extent possible.
Researches, analyzes, and makes recommendations for hardware, software, network and system standards and configurations.
Performs performance analysis, troubleshooting for end user reported issues or reported slowness of application resources and present findings and / or recommendations to upper management.
Participates in project work and KTLO efforts with end user clients, operations, helpdesk, vendors, and other IT technical team members.
Coordinates work efforts with users, operations, helpdesk, vendors, and other technical team members for systems engineering installations and updates.
Prepares system documentation, operational/recovery guides, project plans and status reports for team and management as needed or required.
Provides training to other engineers in line with Systems Engineering Teams Best Practices.
Provides input in improving existing products and procedures and evaluating POCs including collaborating with IT technical teams and end users on IT strategies.

QUALIFICATIONS

Experience with Windows Server System products involving a variety of software and hardware implementations.
Experience with client support in multi-server and multi-environment.
Experience supporting multi-tier applications, as part of client server architecture.
Ability to demonstrate requirements analysis, design, implementation, and maintenance responsibilities for these systems as well as production support of multiple servers.
Experience within an environment of structured life cycle management including change management system and extensive testing prior to implementation.
Must be capable of working in all phases of Windows application deployment in supporting production and development environments, including the ability to troubleshoot, resolve, and recommend technology solutions related to Windows Server and networks.
Experience working as a member of a technical team and/or leading the roll out of production and development systems. This would include assisting in the development and implementation of Policies and Procedures for the production environment as well as overall systems documentation.
Excellent customer service skills required. Excellent business and technical communication skills, both verbal and written. Must read and write English fluently.
Excellent troubleshooting and analytical skills required. Ability to foster an environment that promotes long-term problem avoidance. This is the ability to determine problem sources and implement solutions/policies and procedures that reduce the possibility of problems reoccurring.
Demonstrated leadership in work quality and practices and in mentoring technical team members.
Ability to work proactively, independently, and quickly learn technical and/or conceptual information, identify key issues and details, and present understandable alternatives to both technical and non-technical individuals.
Ability to manage time and priorities with minimal guidance and to respond to multiple and competing deadlines. Ability to work on multiple tasks that are not necessarily well defined, under pressure of full workload, tight deadlines and shifting priorities.

Title: Field Applications Engineer
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

The Provider Management Application Delivery team is responsible for supporting our internal and external customers with applications that provide a seamless user experience in both front-facing and back office environments.

Our team recently launched a fully redesigned Grievance and Appeals application built on the Pega platform and is currently building modernized applications to further enhance our Provider Management user experience. You will collaborate as a Senior Pega Software Engineer with our business, product, and technology teams in an agile development environment to drive how technology enables more efficient business processes and simplified user experiences

RESPONSIBILITIES

Performs as a key contributor to an engineering team that builds and supports exceptional products that provide innovative solutions to challenging business use cases, existing system and operational problems
Participates in architectural design, system analysis, and programming activities on application software; this may often require independent research and study
Develops high-quality and production-ready software by using best-practice data structures, algorithms, design patterns, and frameworks that are maintainable, scalable, responsive, and secure
Writes highest quality code with utmost attention to scalability, security and performance and with an end-to-end mindset from conception to delivery and production support, owning specifications, quality, release deployments and monitoring of production health.
Produces complete, simple, and readable technical documentation for everything developed and maintains a team culture of documenting everything
Tests and ensures quality of all code that developed in line with principles of test-driven development and continuous delivery, utilizing test automation frameworks wherever possible
Participates in code-reviews, provides technical guidance and mentors software engineers
Collaborates closely with Engineering leadership, Product Managers, Designers, Test Automation and other teams and business units to define, prioritize, sequence and scope business and functional requirements and drive results
Instruments infrastructure and application performance monitoring, capacity management, alerting, tools instrumentation and metrics (KPI) management
Performs impact assessment of product (hardware, software) upgrades
Supports and collaborates with other Engineers through evaluation, design analysis, and development phases
Maintains knowledge, ensures competency and compliance with policies and procedures, in order to be the technical expert while collaborating with cross-functional teams
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned

QUALIFICATIONS

Experience designing and developing highly scalable and secure Pega Applications, Healthcare and/or Customer Service capability experience is a plus
Experience with developing and deploying Pega applications on Azure or similar cloud platform
Ability to understand business plans and apply that information into the development of an IT business case
Anticipates problems, resistance or likely objections and takes action to resolve them
Ability to guide, train and mentor associate engineers
Proficient in organizational processes as well as capable of assessing and initiating change of such processes
Demonstrates an in-depth knowledge and application of competency and can consult as well as lead others in its application
Experience integrating legacy systems with the Pega Platform
Experience with Root Cause Analysis in the Pega ecosystem to quickly address and fix system issues
Ability to integrate with external systems of record with the Pega Platform
Ability to understand an existing business process and collaboratively develop a more efficient and automated workflow
Strong communication (written and verbal) and presentation skills
Knowledge of agile development methodologies
Ability to develop and maintain key vendor relationships with a focus on technology currency and best practices
Life-long learner, process improver
Skilled in developing quantitative cost/benefit analysis to measure improvements

Title: Senior DevOps Engineer
Job_Description:
ABOUT US
We are a well-funded Series B ($81MM) high growth startup headquartered in Seattle, with employees throughout the United States and EMEA. Most of our roles are remote-first and we offer a diverse, respectful, fun, and collaborative environment to work in. We're currently in the start-up sweet spot with sufficiently low risk and yet still the potential of massive upside.
At Edge Delta, we are building the world's first edge observability platform allowing our customers to analyze their data as it's created, where it's created. Embracing the freedom to decouple where you analyze your data from where it's stored, this unique take on DevOps, Security, and SRE lets you consume and analyze outputs (logs, metrics, events, traces, telemetry) at the source  how we've defined the edge.

The Senior Data Engineer will design, build, and implement data integration solutions, including data pipelines, data API's, and ETL jobs, to meet the data needs of applications, services, micro services, data assets, and business intelligence and analytical tools. Title: Engine LLP Data & Analytics Specialist
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

This job will be a key contributor in the Market Insights team in support of defining the strategy and vision of Delta Dental's stakeholder ecosystem. The ecosystem includes (but is not limited to) Members, Providers, Clients, Producers. The Senior Customer Insight Analyst will be focused on conducting both quantitative and qualitative research by facilitating customer surveys and forums. This analyst will act as a connector for Market Insights by providing broad reaching analysis and presentations to all levels of leadership throughout the company, and provide thought leadership to move their insights to action across the organization.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Executes within the Customer Insights Team to define and refine research plans, which could include interview guides, participant observation, survey tools, immersive research, SME conversations, surveys and more.
Partners with Marketing and Operations teams to support persona and cohort creation and analysis.
Partners with Customer Experience to support development of customer journey maps with insights and analyses.
Serves as the team's steward of insights and liaison to drive delivery of strategic programs across the organization.
Stays current with and ensures alignment with marketplace trends, innovations within the industry and across other industries.
Identifies known and unknown customer needs and challenges through data analysis, primary and secondary research.
Collaborates with Creative, Branding and Marketing Technology teams for research campaign needs.
Manages repository of research studies and ensure historical context for new learning.
Mentors other Customer Insights team members in areas of sampling, statistical analysis, presentation, and dashboard creation.
Creates reports and analyzes data to identify solutions that meet business goals.
Analyzes current processes and identifies existing or potential problems in order to discover new process improvement opportunities.
This list is not all-inclusive and you are expected to perform other duties as requested or assigned.

QUALIFICATIONS

Minimum Qualifications

4+ w/Bachelor's degree
Additional Experience

Health or dental insurance experience is a plus.
Knowledge, Skills, Abilities

Title: Engine LLP Data & Analytics Specialist
Job_Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION

This job will partner with key business, analytics, and technology stakeholders to identify business challenges, formulate a data plan, drive the insights, and develop solutions to enable the business teams to perform at the highest levels. This individual is responsible for driving understanding and decision making from data, working with key executives down to analysts. This role is part of the Data and Analytics COE which consists of experts and advisors with a specific focus on generating business insight, governing data assets, and promoting the use of data and analytics to achieve business outcome and measurable ROI across the enterprise. The Data Governance Analyst will develop procedures to support the accuracy, security, and integrity of Delta Dental's Data. The role will help maintain best practices regarding data access. Provide expertise, guidance, and support in establishing, operationalizing and sustaining a data governance program that identifies, defines, manages and publishes data standards and policies. The individual will facilitate business processes and guide cross functional Data Stewards in developing enterprise solutions in coordination with IT. In addition, this individual is responsible for identifying, defining and maintaining Data Governance workflows, integrations, master data definitions and corresponding metadata within all represented data domains, ensuring the quality and availability of that data, and coordinating the delivery efforts of that data under proper controls.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Creates objectives/strategies to reflect data governance initiative and charter, working in partnership with cross-functional teams.
Defines, authors and partners with Business, Compliance and Technology stakeholders to operationalize Data Governance Policies, Processes and Procedures.
Partners with Business and Technical Data Stewards to identify, define and maintain data definitions and corresponding metadata across business functions and data domains.
Establishes a Data Quality framework and partners with stakeholders to define and implement data quality rules for multiple Lines of Business.
Performs data analysis and facilitates discussions for data issue/gap identification, root-cause analyses, remediation identification, solution implementation and closure. Documents and reports findings to inform business decisions and prioritize governance needs.
Provides thought leadership and participates with projects that involve any of the upstream or downstream data flows and processes.
Serves as liaison with Business and Data/Technology teams to apply data standards and processes (e.g. data access, classification, quality, certification, metadata, lifecycle and retention, etc.).
Coordinates business interests and collaborates with cross-functional Data Stewards, Compliance, Product and Technology in the development of the Data Governance and Data Management solution.
Leads and/or supports facilitation of workshops, sessions and training to increase Data Governance Awareness and Data Literacy.
Creates and monitors program metrics and dashboard reporting for review and presentation.

QUALIFICATIONS

6+ years of experience in similar roles with a Bachelor's degree or equivalent work experience.
Prior experience directly related to defining, designing, implementing and managing Data Governance, Data Quality, Data Management and Analytics solutions and programs.
Prior experience in a role requiring collaboration across multiple functions within a large, complex organization.
Exceptional analytical, critical thinking, quantitative reasoning, and problem-solving skills with high attention to details and accuracy.
Ability to distill complex concepts into easy-to-understand frameworks and presentations.
Strong business acumen, ability to think strategically and build effective business partnerships.
Ability to clearly define and articulate Enterprise Data Governance Objective.
Direct experience with defining and operationalizing Data Governance Policies, Standards, Processes and Controls (e.g. metadata, data classification, data certification, data access, data retention, lineage etc.).
Experience with Data Governance tools e.g. Collibra to design and build operating model, importing or exporting content, customizing dashboards & widgets, views, creating automation workflows, etc.
Strong functional understanding of data and analytics architecture, platforms, and frameworks; including data modeling, data ingestion, data pipelines (ETL).
Solid understanding of data issues that impact user experience and remediations that need to be implemented to resolve data issues, via business processes and technical capabilities.
Hands-on functional and technical experience in performing data quality, profiling and analysis.
Knowledge of Healthcare and Personal Information Privacy Laws is preferred.
Good familiarity with standard relational database structures, SQL; Tableau and Business Objects nice-to-have.
Strong presentation skills. Should be comfortable with presenting to all levels of management.
Solid planning, priority setting, and project management skills with experience managing multiple projects concurrently.
Ability to lead project teams in driving end to end activities to meet set milestones and provide necessary mentorship/ guidance for the team growth.
A self-starter that adapts well to change in a fast-paced, dynamic workplace and works well in cross-functional teams/projects.
Excellent verbal/written communication skills, including communicating technical issues to non-technical audiences.
